# NxtStps ‚Äî Mobile & responsive (Phase 7)

**Version 1.0 ¬∑ Brand Kit V2.0 ¬∑ Last updated: 2026-04-06**

**Mobile is the default applicant experience** ‚Äî not a shrunk desktop. Design **mobile first**; enhance for larger viewports. Desktop-first CSS overrides are technical debt.

**Source:** [NN/g mobile UX study guide](https://www.nngroup.com/articles/mobile-ux-study-guide/)

## Assumptions (applicant)

5‚Äì7‚Ä≥ screen, **one-handed**, **3G/4G**, **2018‚Äì2021-class** devices, distracted or distressed environments. If it fails here, it is not done.

## Breakpoints (tokens in `app/globals.css`)

Mobile-first base; use **`min-width`** only:

| Token | Width | Typical |
|-------|-------|---------|
| `--bp-sm` | 480px | Large phone / landscape |
| `--bp-md` | 768px | Tablet |
| `--bp-lg` | 1024px | Small laptop / tablet landscape |
| `--bp-xl` | 1280px | Desktop |
| `--bp-2xl` | 1536px | Large desktop |

Example: `@media (min-width: 768px) { ‚Ä¶ }` or `min-width: var(--bp-md)` where supported.

## Touch

- **WCAG 2.2:** ‚â•24px; **NxtStps applicant pathway:** **‚â•44px** ‚Äî see global rules in `globals.css` (Phase 4). Use **`.nxt-icon-button`** when the glyph is small; pad to a 44px hit box.
- **‚â•8px gap** between adjacent targets (`--nxt-touch-target-gap`) ‚Äî use **`.nxt-touch-cluster`** for row/wrap toolbars; prevents mis-taps (including near **Exit Safely**).

## Thumb zone & navigation

- **Primary CTA** on mobile: **bottom of the viewport** ‚Äî prefer **`.nxt-form-actions-mobile`** (sticky bar + safe-area) for long forms, not only the end of scroll.
- **Applicant primary nav:** prefer **bottom bar (‚â§5 items)**; **top bar** for title + back; **hamburger** only for secondary/tertiary ‚Äî not primary applicant IA.
- **Exit Safely:** **top-right**, intentional exception (harder to hit accidentally) ‚Äî Phase 3.

## Performance (accessibility)

Slow 3G / low-end hardware excludes people who need the product most. **Targets:** FCP &lt;1.5s, TTI &lt;3.5s, LCP &lt;2.5s, CLS &lt;0.1 on throttled mobile (directional).

- **Images:** dimensions / `next/image`, lazy below fold, no text-as-image.
- **Fonts:** `display: "swap"` (see `layout.tsx`); subset Latin; extend for Spanish as needed.
- **JS:** route-level splitting; no blocking third-party on applicant paths.
- **CSS:** rely on Tailwind purge in production; avoid shipping huge unused CSS.

## Layout & type

- **&lt;768px:** full-width content, horizontal padding **`var(--space-4)`**; don‚Äôt over-constrain &lt;480px.
- **320px:** single column, **no horizontal page scroll** (WCAG 1.4.10) ‚Äî verify before ship.
- **Body:** **‚â•16px** on mobile ‚Äî never shrink body text for small screens. Heading steps may scale down vs desktop (see Phase 6 / marketing tokens).

## Modals & tables

- **&lt;768px:** prefer **full-screen** dialogs or **bottom sheets** for confirmations ‚Äî not tiny centered modals.
- **Tables** (advocate/agency): responsive ‚Äî simple tables ‚Üí horizontal scroll + sticky first column; complex ‚Üí stacked label:value rows. **No** whole-page horizontal scroll from tables.

## Forms on mobile (with Phase 6)

- **`type` + `inputmode`** for correct keyboards (`tel`, `email`, `numeric`, `decimal`, `date`).
- **autocorrect / autocapitalize / spellcheck** per field type (names vs IDs vs narrative).
- **Viewport:** `width=device-width`, `initial-scale=1`, **`viewport-fit=cover`** ‚Äî **never** `maximum-scale=1` or `user-scalable=no` (root **`viewport` export** in `app/layout.tsx`).

## Testing (before deploy)

Real **Android mid-range** + **iPhone-class** device passes preferred over DevTools-only. Checklist: full applicant path on phone only; targets + spacing; keyboard doesn‚Äôt cover focused field; Exit Safely always reachable; throttled network submit; background/restore; Dynamic Type / TalkBack / VoiceOver on critical flows.

